<sentence id="1"><scope type="spec" id="1"> The chronic immune response in rheumatoid arthritis ( RA ) <cue type="spec" id="1">might</cue> be driven by activated Th1 cells <scope type="neg" id="0"><cue type="neg" id="0">without</cue> sufficient Th2 cell differentiation</scope> to down-modulate inflammation</scope> .</sentence>
<sentence id="2"><scope type="neg" id="2"><cue type="neg" id="2">To</cue> test <scope type="spec" id="3"> <cue type="spec" id="3">whether</cue> disordered memory T cell differentiation contributes to the typical Th1-dominated chronic inflammation in RA</scope> we investigated differentiation of resting CD4+ memory T cells in patients with early ( 6 wk to 12 mo ) untreated RA and in age- and sex-matched healthy controls in vitro</scope> .</sentence>
